Rating: 4
I have been making these for years, and this year I tried using Bob's Red Mill Almond Flour instead of fiddling around grinding my own almonds. It saved time and worked perfectly - I did it by weight, and substituted 9 1/2 ounces of almond flour for the 1 2/3 cups of blanched almonds that the recipe uses for grinding.

Rating: 2
I have to agree with San Francisco: nothing special here. I did give 2 forks for the fact that it is nice to find a cookie that isn't too sweet and does deliver a nice crisp when you bite into it. I'm not sure if I'll put this one in my Christmas boxes this year or not.

