a good cookie, but nothing to write home about. maybe not worth the trouble of all the rolling, cutting, re-refrigerating, etc.

Rating: 4
Made these last year and plan to make again. They are wonderful. I added chocolate to some of the dough, made some raspberry thumbprints. There's so much you can do with this recipe.

Rating: 4
I have always loved these since I first made them, and they are always requested in my holiday gift boxes. I use a fluted cutter in an oval shape (kind of almond shaped.) Everybody always asks for the recipe and can't believe how easy it is! A good one to start shortly after Thanksgiving, freezes well.

Rating: 4
I have been making these since the recipe was published & people RAVE about them. They are light and and packed with subtle almond flavor. I always dip into confectioners sugar. One hint, Roll on wax paper and freeze before cutting as dough gets soft quickly.